<mxfile>
  <diagram name="title" id="page-1">
    <mxGraphModel dx="900" dy="620" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1200" pageHeight="800" math="0" shadow="0" background="#FFFFFF">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="bg" value="" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="0" y="0" width="1200" height="800" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="title" value="NTP 階層と時刻同期" style="text;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=18;fontStyle=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fillColor=none;strokeColor=none;fontColor=#333333;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="400" y="20" width="400" height="36" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!--
          Layout:
            NTP server box at top center: x=450, y=100, w=300, h=60 → center=(600, 130)
            Device boxes below at y=400, h=60 → center y=430
            Vertical distance: 430-130 = 300px > 188px. ✓
            Android: x=150, y=400, w=200, h=60 → center=(250, 430)
            iOS: x=500, y=400, w=200, h=60 → center=(600, 430)
            管理PC: x=850, y=400, w=200, h=60 → center=(950, 430)

          Arrows from NTP center (600,130) to each device:
            Edge to Android center (250,430):
              Diagonal: (600,130)→(250,430)
              Any vertex in the way? iOS box: x=500..700, y=400..460. Check if segment crosses.
              At y=400: t=(400-130)/(430-130)=270/300=0.9. x=600+(250-600)*0.9=600-315=285. 285 < 500. CLEAR.
              No other boxes at that crossing point. ✓

            Edge to iOS center (600,430):
              Vertical: (600,130)→(600,430). Any boxes? None directly in path (Android at x=150..350, 管理PC at x=850..1050).
              Wait: iOS box top at y=400. Segment ends at (600,430) which is inside iOS box. Source/target check: linter skips source+target. ✓

            Edge to 管理PC center (950,430):
              Diagonal: (600,130)→(950,430).
              At y=400: t=0.9. x=600+(950-600)*0.9=600+315=915. iOS box: x=500..700. 915>700. CLEAR.
              At x=700 (iOS box right): t=(700-600)/(950-600)=100/350=0.286. y=130+(430-130)*0.286=130+85.7=215.7. iOS box y=400..460. 215.7<400. CLEAR. ✓

          Label placement: labels at midpoints of each edge.
            Android midpoint: ((600+250)/2, (130+430)/2) = (425, 280).
            iOS midpoint: (600, 280).
            管理PC midpoint: ((600+950)/2, (130+430)/2) = (775, 280).

          Label width of "NTP sync (port 123)": all half-width chars.
            Count: "NTP sync (port 123)" = 19 chars. Width ≈ 19 * 12 * 0.55 = 125.4px. Height ≈ 16.8px.
            Label bboxes (centered at midpoint, w=125.4, h=16.8):
              Android: (425±62.7, 280±8.4) = (362.3..487.7, 271.6..288.4)
              iOS: (600±62.7, 280±8.4) = (537.3..662.7, 271.6..288.4)
              管理PC: (775±62.7, 280±8.4) = (712.3..837.7, 271.6..288.4)
            Do these overlap each other?
              Android bbox right: 487.7. iOS bbox left: 537.3. Gap=49.6px. NO overlap. ✓
              iOS bbox right: 662.7. 管理PC bbox left: 712.3. Gap=49.6px. NO overlap. ✓

          Label bboxes vs other vertices (NTP box, device boxes):
            NTP box: x=450..750, y=100..160.
              Android label: y=271.6..288.4. NTP y=100..160. NO overlap (y ranges separate). ✓
              iOS label: same y. ✓
              管理PC label: same y. ✓
            Device boxes all at y=400..460. Label bboxes at y=271.6..288.4. NO overlap. ✓

          Note box: place to the right at x=900, y=100
            But need to ensure iOS/管理PC edge labels don't overlap note box.
            Note box: x=900, y=80, w=270, h=110 → x=900..1170, y=80..190.
            管理PC edge passes through vicinity. Check if label bbox at (775, 280) overlaps note: y=271.6..288.4 vs 80..190. NO overlap. ✓
            管理PC edge segment (600,130)→(950,430): at x=900, t=(900-600)/(950-600)=300/350=0.857. y=130+(430-130)*0.857=130+257=387. 387 > note_box_bottom=190. CLEAR. ✓
            But does segment cross note box? At y=80: t=(80-130)/(430-130)=-50/300<0. At y=190: t=(190-130)/300=60/300=0.2. x=600+(950-600)*0.2=600+70=670. 670<900. CLEAR. ✓

          OK, this layout works!
        -->

        <!-- Windows Server NTP box (top) -->
        <mxCell id="ntp_server" value="Windows Server NTP" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#333333;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="450" y="100" width="300" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- Device boxes (bottom row) -->
        <mxCell id="android_box" value="ハンディ端末 (Android)" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=#333333;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="150" y="400" width="200" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ios_box" value="ハンディ端末 (iOS)" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=#333333;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="500" y="400" width="200" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="pc_box" value="管理 PC" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=#333333;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="850" y="400" width="200" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- Note box (right side) -->
        <mxCell id="note_box" value="CFG-010: max_clock_skew = 5 秒&#xa;超過時 ERR-VAL-010 を発行" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=#333333;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="900" y="80" width="270" height="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!--
          Arrows: ntp_server -> each device
          Using source/target vertex IDs. Linter uses vertex centers.
          Source center: ntp_server = (600, 130). Target centers: android=(250,430), ios=(600,430), pc=(950,430).

          Edge ntp->android: (600,130)→(250,430). No waypoints needed, diagonal is clear.
          Edge ntp->ios: (600,130)→(600,430). Vertical, clear.
          Edge ntp->pc: (600,130)→(950,430). No waypoints needed, diagonal is clear.
          BUT: need to check note_box crossing for pc edge.
            note_box: x=900..1170, y=80..150.
            Segment (600,130)→(950,430): at x=900, t=0.857, y=387. 387>150. clear.
            At y=80: t<0 (out of range). At y=150: t=(150-130)/(430-130)=20/300=0.067. x=600+350*0.067=623.3. 623.3<900. CLEAR. ✓

          However, the label bboxes for ios and pc edges:
            ios midpoint: (600, 280). label bbox: x=537.3..662.7.
            Does this overlap note_box? note_box x=900..1170. 662.7<900. CLEAR. ✓
        -->
        <mxCell id="edge_ntp_android" value="NTP sync (port 123)" style="endArrow=classic;endFill=1;html=1;strokeColor=#333333;edgeStyle=none;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=#333333;" edge="1" parent="1" source="ntp_server" target="android_box">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <mxCell id="edge_ntp_ios" value="NTP sync (port 123)" style="endArrow=classic;endFill=1;html=1;strokeColor=#333333;edgeStyle=none;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=#333333;" edge="1" parent="1" source="ntp_server" target="ios_box">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <mxCell id="edge_ntp_pc" value="NTP sync (port 123)" style="endArrow=classic;endFill=1;html=1;strokeColor=#333333;edgeStyle=none;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=#333333;" edge="1" parent="1" source="ntp_server" target="pc_box">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
